What are the benefits of fat transfer/grafting? Fat contains the highest number of stem cells in the adult body. Adipose tissue-derived stem cells (ADSCs) which can turn into fat, cartilage, muscle, bone, and tendon, among other cell lineages. Their regenerative capacity is unrivaled, and are useful to treat scars, deformations, and trauma or augment body parts (breast, buttock). When the Liposuction procedure is complete, we clothe our patient a special corset before s/he comes out of anestheisa. Thus we keep swellings and bruises at minimum level. Besides it will help body to take the desired shape during the healing period. The corset should be weared for 2-4 weeks except the times when taking shower. Post-op process is rather confortable and painless.
One of the greatest benefit of the procedure is to enable tightening and recovery of the skin. These benefits are the main reasons that this technique is created and used by the doctors. The other benefit of this procedure is that the healing process is quite fast.
Patients can return back to their daily lives after the same day of the operation, especially after liposunctions applied to a single area. In case of procedures which are applied to 2-3 areas, patients can return back to normal life after resting 3-4 days. Post-op bruises,swellings, time required for wearing corset and returning to daily routine is faster than classic techniques. The patient may start light workouts and exercises after 10th day. Ä°t is recommended to start heavy workouts after 3rd week. Post-op bruises disappear between 10th and 14th day. Swellings caused by the operation decreases after 3rd week. By this means you can notice the differences in your body after the 3rd week. However, remember that the processs of reshaping will take 6 months to fully complete.
